# Dependency Rules

- Add dependencies only to modules. Don`t add dependencies to the parent pom
- Prefer Spring Boot managed dependency versions.
- Do not add libraries that duplicate existing capabilities.
- Explain every new dependency in one sentence.
- Prefer test-scoped dependencies when possible.
- Prefer Boot starters over manual dependency assembly when appropriate.
- Keep runtime dependency graph minimal and explicit.
